The cargo found at the transit shed was loose dried fish and 33 cans weighing 3 litres each that tested positive for Crystal Meth. Image by: Supplied The South African Revenue Service has seized 100kg of crystal meth worth R30-million at OR Tambo International airport. Drug smugglers hid the huge consignment in three-litre vegetable oil cans amid boxes of loose dried fish. The drugs were confiscated on Friday at an airport transit shed. Sars spokesman Sandile Memela said the shipment had come from Cameroon via Istanbul before landing in Johannesburg. Police were investigating said Memela. Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share